In Gloamport’s sugar-ash fog, three powers trade favors like candied knives. The **Brass Lantern Guild** tends gaslights and “keeps citizens safe,” yet quietly tunes lantern-hums to map—then cage—overlooked places before cartographers can name them. The **Soot-Sweet Carnival Combine** arrives with calliope cheer and missing children found… for a fee; backstage, it bargains in nursery rhymes, stitching binding verses into coats to leash shadows and smuggle doors between streets. Beneath both, the **Inkbone Archivists** run humble map-repair stalls, but hoard torn atlas pages, compiling a “complete” world by erasing what shouldn’t exist. The Guild buys Carnival routes; the Carnival blackmails Archivists; the Archivists poison both with false coordinates.

